A Nairobi court has issued a warrant of arrest for Magarini MP Harrison Kombe for failing to repay a soft loan from former Molo MP Macharia Mukiri in 2008.The warrant was issued by senior resident magistrate Issac Orenge of Milimani Commercial Court, to be executed by Nairobi county commissioner.The court was told despite several attempts to have Kombe pay the loan &ldquo;he has flatly declined&rdquo;.Orenge issued a decree against the MP on January 11.